meVE.Aposticha1.mode = misc_en_UK_lash.Mode2
meVE.Aposticha1.melody = misc_en_UK_lash.Idiomelon
meVE.Aposticha1.text = "Herald of repentance, John Baptist, when your head was struck off you sanctified the earth; because you made clear God’s law to the faithful and utterly destroyed lawlessness. As you stand before the throne of Christ the King of heaven, implore him to have mercy on our souls."

meVE.Aposticha2.mode = misc_en_UK_lash.Mode2
meVE.Aposticha2.melody = misc_en_UK_lash.Idiomelon
meVE.Aposticha2.text = "For the law of the Lord your head was struck off, all-holy John. With blameless boldness of speech you rebuked the impious king when he transgressed the law. And so the hosts of Angels marvel at you; the choirs of Apostles and Martyrs glorify you; we too honour your yearly memorial, as we glorify the Holy Trinity, who crowned you, blessed Forerunner."

meVE.Aposticha3.mode = misc_en_UK_lash.Mode2
meVE.Aposticha3.melody = misc_en_UK_lash.Idiomelon
meVE.Aposticha3.text = "The Prophet from a Prophet, who became greater than the Prophets, who was sanctified from his mother’s womb for the service of the Lord, had his head struck off today by a lawless king; and both before his execution and after it clearly rebuking the maiden who danced licentiously, he put the regiment of sin to shame. And so we cry out: Baptist John, as you have freedom to speak, intercede insistently for our souls."

meVE.AposGlory.mode = misc_en_UK_lash.Mode8
meVE.AposGlory.melody = misc_en_UK_lash.Idiomelon
meVE.AposGlory.text = "Forerunner of the Saviour, you rebuked kings that they should not act lawlessly; and so the little darling of a lawless woman persuaded Herod to cut off your head, and therefore from the rising of the sun to its setting your name is to be praised. As you have freedom before the Lord intercede insistently for our souls."

meVE.AposTheotokion.mode = misc_en_UK_lash.Mode8
meVE.AposTheotokion.melody = ""
meVE.AposTheotokion.text = "Virgin without bridegroom, who conceived God ineffably in the flesh, Mother of God Most High, accept the supplications of your servants, O all-blameless, who bestow on all cleansing from faults. Now accept our entreaties and implore that we may all be saved."

meVE.Apolytikion1.mode = misc_en_UK_lash.Mode2
meVE.Apolytikion1.melody = ""
meVE.Apolytikion1.text = "The just is remembered with praises, but for you the Lord’s testimony suffices, O Forerunner; for you were declared more praiseworthy than the Prophets, because you were found worthy to baptize in running streams the One they had proclaimed. Therefore, having struggled bravely for the truth with joy, you preached to those in Hell a God who had appeared in flesh, who takes away the sin of the world, and grants us his great mercy."

